<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="711" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.111/63.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                    Turkey</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 138.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith
                            copy and translation of a note verbale received yesterday from the
                            Sublime Porte, asking the assistance of the United States Government in
                            securing from the Government of Haiti licenses to vendors of Ottoman
                            nationality residing in the Island of Haiti.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.],</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William W. Rockhill.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Ministry for Foreign
                                        Affairs</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                        Embassy</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sublime Porte</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-15">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Imperial Ministry for Foreign Affairs is informed that the
                                Haitian Government raises great difficulties in the matter of the
                                renewal of licenses to retail merchants of foreign, and particularly
                                of Ottoman, nationality.</p>
                            <p>As the Representative of the French Republic has already taken steps
                                towards removing these difficulties, the Imperial Ministry will be
                                obliged to the Embassy of the United States of America if it will
                                kindly use its good offices with its Government to the end that the
                                Representative of the United States in Haiti may be invited to join
                                in these steps.</p>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>